cs.ET, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

The paper proposes machine learning-based approaches to optimize variational quantum circuits for solving combinatorial problems. This involves using reinforcement learning and kernel density estimation techniques to learn optimal QAOA parameters. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which covers new and emerging technologies in computer science. The paper also involves machine learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, which could place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
